name: DRAPER STRIPE - THE EARLY STUFF
description: DRAPER STRIPE is a playful take on pinstripes and men’s suiting fabrics. Materially rich, the wallcovering features a ground of fine, cotton-linen blend string yarn accented by saturated paper yarns. This small-scale stripe brings a refined pop of color to any space. Color variations and subtle irregularities are inherent to this wallpaper’s natural fibers and artisanal beauty. Priced by the yard, starting at $53/yard. Sold in eight yard rolls.

name: BACKDROP PAINTER'S STRIPE - ROCOCO
description: BACKDROP PAINTER’S STRIPE is a bold vertical stripe made from textured paper yarns. Each 9” stripe, the same size as a paint roller, is an organically beautiful arrangement of paper yarns on a slightly sheened ground. Named after Backdrop paint colors, each colorway reflects our signature palette in material form. Color variations and subtle irregularities are inherent to this wallpaper’s artisanal beauty. Priced by the yard, starting at $95/yard. Sold in eight yard rolls.

name: TOILE DE FEMMES - POPPY
description: Toile De Femmes is a lyrical, contemporary wallpaper designed by Barrie Benson and Chandra Johnson of Peg Norriss in collaboration with Schumacher. Featuring hand-drawn female motifs by celebrated artist Jackie Gendel, this modern twist on classic toile wallpaper celebrates bold femininity, timeless craftsmanship, and artistic storytelling. Showcased in HBO's Sex and the City sequel, And Just Like That, this statement-making pattern captures whimsical vignettes of women at leisure, riding horses, and practicing archery. Perfect for accent walls, powder rooms, and creative interiors, Toile De Femmes is an elevated, artful design that blends history with modern style. Priced by the yard, starting at $117/yard. Sold in ten yard rolls.

name: APPIAN WAY PANEL SET - FOG
description: Inspired by the legendary road to Rome, APPIAN WAY PANEL SET is a transportive hand-painted scenic panorama by artist Xavier Donnelly. A landscape of ruins, monuments, and villas painted in rich detail creates a sense of mystery and surprise throughout the design. At 15’ tall by 16’ wide, the scenic mural moves from dense forest to layered architecture to billowing clouds, trimmable for any room. The dramatic scale and stunning painted texture capture the feeling of a fresco painted directly on the wall. Priced as a panel set, starting at $2,789/set of four. SEE THE PARTNERSHIP HERE.

name: WABI-SABI - MOSS
description: Simple geometries are arranged to achieve perfect imperfection. Inspired and named from the Japanese aesthetic philosophy, WABI-SABI brings texture and subtle color to the forefront with tonal shifts ebbing and flowing in a rhythmic mid-scale design. Made from original painted artwork. Also available in Peel & Stick in Moss colorway. Priced by the yard, starting at $34/yard. Sold in ten yard rolls.
